==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tirailleur
<hw>Ti`rail`leur"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., from
<ets>tirailler</ets> to skirmish, wrest, from <ets>tirer</ets> to
draw.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>Formerly, a member of an independent
body of marksmen in the French army. They were used sometimes in front
of the army to annoy the enemy, sometimes in the rear to check his
pursuit. The term is now applied to all troops acting as
skirmishers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tire</ent>⟦br⟧
